96.4	Sardinia	Sardinia	Sardinia is the second largest island in the Mediterranean Sea, with an area of 23,821 km². It is situated between 38° 51' and 41° 15' latitude north and 8° 8' and 9° 50' east longitude. To the west of Sardinia is the Balearic Sea, a unit of the Mediterranean Sea; to Sardinia's east is the Tyrrhenian Sea, which is also an element of the Mediterranean Sea.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Bandiera_ufficiale_RAS.svg/100px-Bandiera_ufficiale_RAS.svg.png
